Type>General</Type><Text>The B.O.G Hotel is designed with a unique combination of luxurious textures and colors inspired by Colombia's two greastest natural treasures; gold and emeralds. The imagination of the famed Portuguese designer Nini Andrade has captured their luster in shades of bronze, green, and grey in a concept that makes this hotel unlike any other-proud to proclaim its selection as the first Colombian hotel to be chosen as a Design Hotel. After a day discovering the vibrant surroundings, the rooftop's heated swimming pool offers a welcome respite, with views over the city.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>SurroundingArea</Type><Text>B.O.G. Hotel is located in one of the capital's most exclusive sectors but only a few minutes from the financial center and a short stroll away from exclusive boutiques and shopping malls and the finest in gourmet dining. The hotel is located 20 minutes from El Dorado International Airport.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>RoomTypes</Type><Text>All 55 rooms by award-winning designer Nini Andrade Silva focus on bronze, green, greys and beige combined with natural stone, bronze, mirrors, mosaics and tinted glass to create pared back and restful spaces. While the in-room decor is intentionally simple, every comfort is assured, including soundproofed windows, 500-thread linens and bathroom products and scents that have been exclusively designed for the hotel.</Text></Description><Description><Language>en</Language><Type>DiningFacilities</Type><Text>The Restaurant La Leo, Cocina Mestiza will offer very special breakfasts and a selection of light meals directed as discriminating palates interested in more informal dining. The Lounge Bar offers a unique atmosphere for enjoying a cocktail or a drink and boasts the finest in musical accompaniment. There is also a Terrace Bar near the pool on the roof top which is ideal for enjoying a drink while admiring the view in the open air. This 9th floor heated pool is completed by a deck which looks out upon the green mountains that rise above the city, and the terrace itself offers a romantic setting for cocktail parties and other social events.</Text></Description><Amenity><Code>Parking</Code><Text>Parking</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>Safe</Code><Text>Safe</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>FitnessFacility</Code><Text>Fitness facility</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>InHouseDining</Code><Text>Hotel restaurant</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>InHouseBar</Code><Text>Hotel bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>MiniBarInRoom</Code><Text>Mini-bar</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>RoomService</Code><Text>Room service</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>HairDryer</Code><Text>Hair dryer</Text></Amenity><Amenity><Code>AirConditionedRooms</Code><Text>Air-conditioned rooms</Text></Amenity><Rating><System>Stars</System><Score>50</Score><Description>Five star</Description></Rating><Rank>1</Rank></HotelElement>